TITLE: The market is looking for the next 'domino' to fall, keeping banks under pressure
SUMMARY: The sharp selloff in regional banks sparked by the March failure of Silicon Valley Bank resumed Tuesday, catching Wall Street analysts and investors off guard.

TITLE: FDA approves GSK's RSV vaccine for older adults, world's first shot against virus
SUMMARY: The FDA's approval is a victory for GSK in a race against Pfizer and Moderna to bring a shot that targets respiratory syncytial virus to the market.

TITLE: UAW withholding Biden re-election endorsement until EV concerns are addressed
SUMMARY: UAW President Shawn Fain says the union wants a "just transition" for workers, as the government uses taxpayer money to subsidize the EV industry.

TITLE: McDonald's franchisees fined after 305 minors, including 10-year-olds, found working illegally
SUMMARY: Two 10-year-olds were among over 300 minors found to be working in violation of federal labor laws at McDonald's franchises across Kentucky and other states.

TITLE: J&J's consumer health business, Kenvue, is going public this week. Here's what to know
SUMMARY: J&J's consumer health spinoff, Kenvue, is expected to set an initial public offering price Wednesday night and trade Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange.

TITLE: Olive Garden owner Darden Restaurants buys Ruth's Chris Steak House for $715 million
SUMMARY: Ruth's Chris Steak House has more than 150 locations worldwide and generated $505.9 million in revenue in 2022.

TITLE: Yum Brands earnings miss estimates despite KFC and Pizza Hut's recovery in China
SUMMARY: Yum's same-store sales increased 8% in the quarter as KFC, Taco Bell and Pizza Hut outperformed expectations.

TITLE: CVS beats on earnings and revenue but lowers profit outlook
SUMMARY: CVS lowered its earnings outlook due to costs associated with recent acquisitions.

TITLE: Mortgage demand drops as bank failures hit jumbo loan rates
SUMMARY: Mortgage demand dropped last week despite a slight easing in interest rates, while trouble in the banking sector makes jumbo loans more expensive.

TITLE: Eli Lilly Alzheimer’s treatment donanemab slowed disease progression in clinical trial
SUMMARY: Donanemab, a monthly antibody infusion made by pharmaceutical company Eli Lilly, also significantly reduced brain plaque associated with Alzheimer's disease.

TITLE: Starbucks earnings beat as China reverses same-store sales declines
SUMMARY: Starbucks said its same-store sales climbed 11% in its fiscal second quarter.

TITLE: Ford posts stellar first quarter, boosted by fleet and legacy truck divisions
SUMMARY: Ford is reporting its quarterly financial results by business unit, instead of by region, for the first time.

TITLE: Hollywood writers are on strike — here's what it means for TV and movie production
SUMMARY: Writers are seeking more compensation to reflect the content boom driven by streaming over the past several years.

TITLE: Gilead Sciences battles U.S. government in court over HIV prevention patent
SUMMARY: The U.S. claims Gilead's drugs Truvada and Descovy infringe on CDC patents.

TITLE: Wall Street is cutting more jobs as Morgan Stanley plans 3,000 layoffs
SUMMARY: For Morgan Stanley and others, the cuts show Wall Street is wrangling with a slump that's dragging on for longer than expected

TITLE: Restaurant Brands earnings beats estimates, fueled by Tim Hortons' and Burger King's strong sales
SUMMARY: Burger King's U.S. same-store sales climbed 8.7%, an early sign that its turnaround is taking hold.

TITLE: Pfizer earnings and revenue top expectations despite Covid vaccine sales decline
SUMMARY: Pfizer's quarterly earnings topped analysts' expectations, despite a sales decline driven by the lower demand for the company's Covid vaccine.

TITLE: New York and California lost over $90 billion in income to low-tax states during Covid
SUMMARY: The losses accelerated the trend of high-earners relocating to lower-tax states like Florida and Texas.

TITLE: Ford cutting price of electric Mustang Mach-E by thousands of dollars
SUMMARY: Ford will lower pricing of the Mach-E by $1,000 to $4,000. The cuts will make the starting price of the vehicle be between $42,995 and $59,995.

TITLE: Home prices are back on the rise as the spring market proves more competitive than expected
SUMMARY: A sharp drop in new listings, adding to an already meager supply of homes for sale, is leading to renewed bidding wars.

TITLE: Lordstown Motors warns of bankruptcy after Foxconn threatens to walk away from crucial funding deal
SUMMARY: After buying Lordstown's factory last year, Foxconn agreed to invest an additional $170 million. That deal is now in jeopardy, the embattled startup said.

TITLE: Lawmakers praise First Republic sale, but efforts to pass new bank rules are fizzling
SUMMARY: Interest on Capitol Hill in tightening bank regulations appears to have waned amid the failure of another institution, First Republic.

TITLE: Lawmakers urge SEC to crack down on Chinese retail giant Shein over alleged forced labor
SUMMARY: Shein, a major fast-fashion brand, is under fire for allegedly selling clothes made by forced labor in China.

TITLE: FAA launches faster, high-altitude flight routes to avoid congestion along the East Coast
SUMMARY: The FAA estimated that the new routes would reduce about 6,000 minutes of travel time a year.

TITLE: DeSantis Disney oversight board votes to sue company over tax-district fight
SUMMARY: DeSantis is battling Disney as he is considered a leading potential contender against ex-President Donald Trump for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination.

TITLE: Jamie Dimon says 'this part of the crisis is over' after JPMorgan Chase buys First Republic
SUMMARY: JPMorgan Chase, which acquired banking assets in the 2008 financial crisis, just won an auction to gain even more size with the takeover of First Republic.

TITLE: Facebook was the main donor to a group that fought antitrust reforms in 2020 and 2021
SUMMARY: Facebook donated $34 million to pro-tech industry group American Edge Project as the nonprofit took on antitrust legislation.

TITLE: Bipartisan attorneys general call on Medicare to cover Alzheimer's treatments
SUMMARY: Attorneys general from 23 states, the District of Columbia, and two U.S. territories called on Medicare to cover Alzheimer's treatments without restrictions.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase takes over First Republic after biggest U.S. bank failure since 2008
SUMMARY: JPMorgan acquired all of First Republic's deposits and a "substantial majority of assets." Its shares rose 2.6% in premarket trading on the news.

TITLE: American Airlines pilots vote for potential strike while airline says negotiations are progressing
SUMMARY: American Airlines says the end of contract negotiations is "in sight."
